caption: AMAZING food at a great price. Their al pastor tacos and burrito are my favorite in the entire city. Their staff is always so nice and they are SO quick!  Once I ordered a single taco to go and they had it ready before I could finish handing them the cash to pay!

We go to Moran pretty regularly, and this review is way over due. Most recently, we used them for our COVID backyard wedding, and the owner, Pepe, went above and beyond to make our experience great. He personally delivered to us even though we know he was short staffed, and fulfilled every one of our wishes to try and keep our family safe while we were celebrating. The food was AMAZING as usual. The good reviews are fake and bought reviews!!! The people posting 5 stars have 1 review??? Vegetarians BEWARE! Just moved to the Logan Sq. area and trying out some new places. Came here on a very busy Friday night. The waiter and waitress were very friendly and welcoming. I found some ground beef in our complimentary salsa. I let our waiter know he said sorry and he will bring us another. It never came. I asked for recommendations on vegetarian food. He recommended the veggie salad which has refried beans. I asked if they were vegetarian, the answer was no, they are cooked in lard. I'm very limited on options now. So I ordered vegetarian quesadillas because you really can't go wrong with that right? I was wrong. They were lacking flavor and I don't even think the onion and green pepper had a sprinkle of salt. My husband who only eats seafood ordered Shrimp Diablo which comes with fries and rice for 13.99. He asked for extra fries since the rice has chicken stock. When his dish came, both of our jaws dropped. It came with about 7 pieces of medium size shrimp drenched in some type of a sauce, some ice berg lettuce and a very small amount of fries that had some lagging pieces of tortilla chips. The presentation was just horrible. The food all together was subpar, the waiter and waitress were very nice but very overwhelmed at the same time. (The waitress tripped on someone and a whole glass of water fell on me which I didn't complain because everyone makes mistakes and I'm not sure she was at fault). It seemed like most people were there for the drinks, not so much the food. I won't be returning..
